#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.68"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.68:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.68:0.2"
msgid "7. Pattakammavagga"
msgstr "7. Deeds of Substance"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.68:0.3"
msgid "68. Devadattasutta"
msgstr "68. Devadatta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.68:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante "
"devadatte."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left."

msgctxt "an4.68:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta:"

msgctxt "an4.68:1.3"
msgid "“attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"“Possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and "
"downfall."

msgctxt "an4.68:1.4"
msgid "Parābhavāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.68:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ "
"deti;"
msgstr "It’s like a banana tree …"

msgctxt "an4.68:2.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko "
"udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.68:3.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;"
msgstr "or a bamboo …"

msgctxt "an4.68:3.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko "
"udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.68:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;"
msgstr "or a reed, all of which bear fruit to their own ruin and downfall …"

msgctxt "an4.68:4.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko "
"udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.68:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya "
"gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti;"
msgstr "It’s like a mule, which becomes pregnant to its own ruin and downfall."

msgctxt "an4.68:5.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko "
"udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādīti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for "
"his own ruin and downfall."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.1"
msgid "Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti,"
msgstr "The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.2"
msgid "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ;"
msgstr "as are the bamboo and the reed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.3"
msgid "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti,"
msgstr "Honor destroys a wretch,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.4"
msgid "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti."
msgstr "as pregnancy destroys a mule.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.68:6.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
